'''
# Create a set of card                                              
cards = matrix(data = 0,
                nrow = 13,
               ncol  = 4)

colnames(cards) = sort(c('Hearts','Clubs','Spades','Diamonds'))

# Let's shuffle and pick a handful (5 cards)
random_cards    = sample(1:(13*4))[1:5]
cards[random_cards] = 1
'''

# Using sample() to shuffle is a smart way to do. And I'm sure there are other ways. Wait til I find out
